    {
        "content": "<p>What about <code>Classical.choose (p := fun ... ↦ ...) &lt;| exists_uncurry.mp (t p)</code>?</p>",
        "id": 497166517,
        "sender_full_name": "Jz Pan",
        "timestamp": 1738418063
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think you mean <code>Classical.choose (p := fun x ↦ p x.1 x.2) &lt;| Prod.exists.mp (t p)</code>? (there is no <code>exists_uncurry</code> in Mathlib yet)? There will be type mismatch anyway.</p>",
        "id": 497167035,
        "sender_full_name": "Michał Staromiejski",
        "timestamp": 1738418526
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You just need <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Prod.exists%27#doc\">docs#Prod.exists'</a></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">noncomputable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now_ok</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">×</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">β</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Classical</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">choose</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Prod</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">exists'</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mpr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 497168733,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1738420127
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This actually works and I guess it's synthesising the parameter <code>p</code>. Thanks a lot.</p>",
